  "category_subtitle": "Learn how to count machines and vehicles in Japanese using 台",
  "category_detail": "<b>Counting Machines in Japanese</b><br><br>In Japanese, machines and mechanical devices are counted using the counter <b>「台」(だい / dai)</b>.<br><br>This counter is used for things such as <b>cars, computers, televisions, smartphones, cameras, refrigerators, washing machines, and other mechanical equipment</b>.<br><br><b>Basic Pattern</b><br>Most numbers follow the simple pattern:<br><span class=\"example\">number + 台</span><br><br>Examples:<br><span class=\"example\">1台</span> <span class=\"romaji\">(いちだい / ichidai)</span><br><span class=\"example\">2台</span> <span class=\"romaji\">(にだい / nidai)</span><br><span class=\"example\">3台</span> <span class=\"romaji\">(さんだい / sandai)</span><br><br><b>Common Usage</b><br><span class=\"example\">車が三台あります。</span> <span class=\"romaji\">(kuruma ga sandai arimasu)</span><br>Meaning: There are three cars.<br><br>This counter has a very regular pronunciation pattern and is easy for learners.",
